  "text": "The verification and validation of the established models are performed according to [CITATION_1] . Two various meshes consisting of $540 000 and 590 000 cells for the exhaust fume hood model are used to asses the sensitivity of numerical solutions to the number of cells. The last one has more cells inside the fume hood. Predicted velocity profiles at y/H 5 0.125, 0.375, 0.625 and 0.875 in front of the sash are compared and shown in Figs 6 and 7 for 100 and 75% open cases. As a result, those predicted velocity profiles by those meshes are very close. Hence, the grid independence exists in those solutions. The mesh consisting of $540 000 cells is enough to obtain a grid-independent solution.",
